{"id":"project-LICHEN-a2t4","title":"coap_status.c: CBOR encoding functions lack buffer bounds checking","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_status.c
Lines: 159-280, 282-332, 334-392

The CBOR encoding helper functions (cbor_put_tstr, cbor_put_key, cbor_put_uint, etc.) write to buffer without checking bounds. The encoder functions check buf_size once at entry but continue writing without validating that each write fits:

```c
size_t lichen_coap_encode_status_cbor(uint8_t *buf, size_t buf_size, ...)
{
    if (buf_size < LICHEN_COAP_STATUS_CBOR_MAX_SIZE) {
        return 0;
    }
    // All subsequent writes assume space is available
    cbor_put_map_header(buf, &off, map_count);
    cbor_put_key(buf, &off, "uptime_s");  // No bounds check
    ...
}
```

If LICHEN_COAP_STATUS_CBOR_MAX_SIZE is underestimated or caller passes larger buf_size, buffer overrun is possible.

Impact: SECURITY - potential buffer overflow in CBOR encoding.

